* Game Ideas
- Kaiju roguelike
  - big, multi-tile monsters
    - direct hit from kaiju, obscene amount of damage, almost always insta-death
    = kaiju more often do environment damage, and chunks of terrain etc can hit the player
  - level structure
    - lots of obstacles, buildings, etc
    - the remains of tokyo after the kaiju showed up
    - streets, alleys
    - you can hide in a building, but kaiju can break down the building
    - every building has an escape/back door/etc
    - one giant map
    - you need several maguffins to put together to destroy the kaiju breeding grounds
    - the maguffins attract kaiju, so progression
    - use perlin noise or something to create a kaiju density map
  - terrain features
    - buildings
    - parks
    - highways that restrict movement with controlled access
    - vending machines
      - money operated
      - usually heal you (random)
      - some random positive effect sometimes
      - unknown finite uses
  - vehicle-based movement
    - motorcycle:
      - 2x1
      - draw as:   %@
      - wasd to move
      - you have a speed and a facing
        - reticle for indicator
      - moving along with your facing increases your speed
        - diminishing return on acceleration? (maybe not)
          - ie accel 1 -> speed 2, accel 3 -> speed 3, accel 6 -> speed 4
      - a right turn halves your speed
      - a reverse brakes
        - braking continues for speed/2
        - causes the motorcycle to turn right/left
        - speed goes to 0
      - use the shift keys to modify movement
        - shift + brake is a weaker brake
        - shift + left/right strafes
        - shift + forward maintains speed
      - when dismouting at speed:
        motorcycle travels distance equal to current speed this turn
        next turn it swerves and tips over. travels half its speed then stops
      - crash:
        - separated from motorcycle
        - need to walk back to it (normal 4-dir mvoement)
        - on the turn you would have crashed, you leap off the motorcycle and let it crash instead
          - you do not move
          - the motorcycle does
          - motorcycle loses some hp
            - at zero, its broken
        - same if you send it into a kaiju
          - damage to enemy proportional to speed

mapgen:
  - there's a cool thing that happens in cities:
    when you have two different neighborhoods on grid systems, but the grids are at different angles and they meet
  - generating by chunks of city blocks
    - they vary in some way:
      - all grids are NSEW aligned
      - street width, in any direction
      - street spacing (controls block width, height)
      - building size
      - what % of a block is building/open
      - degree of destruction
      - zoning
        - residential 
          - more vending machines, smaller buildings
        - industrial
          - larger buildings, more kaiju eggs
        - commercial
          - more loot, piles of money
        - kaiju nest
          - how do we indicate to the player that it is a kaiju nest?
  - map features
    - obstacles
      - abandoned cars (3x3)
        - player does not have the right kind of license and won't drive a car
      - partially destroyed car
      - fire hydrants
      - rubble
      - potholes
      - trees
      - downed aircraft
    - trail of destruction
    - vending machines
    - kaiju eggs
    - piles of money
    - weapons/trinkets

eg blocks are 50x50

car:
  O-O
  | |
  O-O

motorcycle (unoccupied):
  O%
motorcycle (occupied):
  @%

terrain types:
  - " grass
  - asphalt
    - painted asphalt (for road stripes)
  - . interior
  - ^ tree
  - & rubble (impassable to player, passable to monster)
  - ; debris (slows)
  - 0 eggs (monsters do not destroy, impassable to monsters, player can run them over)
  - fat + glass door
    - shoot it to break it
    - can crash through it
  - + wooden door
    - open/closed
  - # wall
  - = glass wall / window
    - shoot it to break it
    - can crash through it
  - damaging terrain?
  - * broken glass
    - damage when walking on it?


motorcycles:
 - lots of spare motorcycles scattered throughout the map
 - they have varying attributes
   - model name
   - hp
   - damage
   - top speed
   - acceleration curve
     - eg: [1,1,1,1,1,1] accel by 1 at any speed
     - eg: [3,1,1,1,1,1] accel by 3 from a stop, otherwise by 1
     - eg: [2,2,2,2,1]
     - instead of throwing these numbers at the player, display a "horsepower"
       and make the exact curve discovered


2500 x 2500 -> 50 blocks x 50 blocks (2500 blocks)



- "gun-type"
   base damage + N scaling damage
   driven by consecutive attacks on the same enemy
   - params:
      - base
      - scale
- "explosive-type"
  some larger flat base damage
  some area
  - hits every space of its area
  - a larger dude can get hit more times
   - params:
      - damage
      - area
- "poison type"
  applies a debuff
  the debuff grows over time (exponential? logistic?)
  the debuff increases incoming damage
   - params:
      - damage
- "radioactive type"
  percent current enemy hp
   - params:
      - damage
- "psychic type"
  doing overkill to enemies gains psychic charge
  damage dealt is based on psychic charge
  (maybe its spent, maybe not)
  charge decays over time
  - the map has low hp kaiju eggs that count for this
  - params:
    - damage
- "motorcycle type"
  - Damage is proportional to square of speed
  - if the kaiju has low enough remaining health and you drive into it, you just go through

- trinkets:
  - labubu (..variants)
  - cell phone
  - figurine (..variants)
    - maybe these pop out of vending machines sometimes
  - pencil case
  - omamori
  - talisman
  - amulet
  - sakazuki
  - hachimaki
  - briefcase
  - hair clip
  - juzu beads
  - credit card
  - stamp seal
  - ...



- weapons:
  - gun
    - basic shot does 1 damage
    - sometimes it becomes useful somehow
  - artillery strike
    - paint target for N turns
    - then the artillery lands
  - paint to target a missile?
  - paint to target a nuclear weapon?
  - poisonous dart (engineered anti-kaiju virus)
    - takes time to take effect
  - death ray (radiation damage)
    - restrictions: splashback, not affected by multipliers
  - regeneration inhibitor:
    - increases damage of subsequent attacks
    - has a cooldown
    - the bonuses are color-coded
  - psi lance
    - has bonus damage based on overkill delivered to other enemies recently

- game about compounding numbers
  - damage types:
     radiation: does a percentage of current enemy health
     viral: over time, stacks up an increasing multiplier on incoming damage
     combo: a sequence of moves that increase the damage of immediately (ish) following moves
     overkill: bonus damage to later attacks from excess damage dealt to other enemies
     crit clock: 
       - clock 1: 2x damage every other turn
       - clock 2: 2x damage every 3rd turn
       - clock 3: 2x damage every 5rd turn
       - ...

- progression:
  - Your level is the size of the biggest kaiju you have taken down
  - higher level means you can carry more items
  - items in inventory have an order (or not?)

- stats and damage:
  - kaiju hp
    - 10^n
  - player stats:
      10 - 40 or so?

- types of items:
  - crit clock (3,4,5)
  - motorcycle acceleration
  - motorcycle impact damage (to target)
  - debris resist (maybe it usually slows you)
  - [damage modifiers]
  - vending machine detector
  - vending luck adjust
  - egg detector
  - kaiju detection
  - money detector
  - street map
  - motorcycle armor
  - consumable heal
    - auto eat when at critical hp
  - something that lets you drive through walls
  - atm card?
  - dna sequencer
    - grows in stats when breaking special eggs

- vision
  - obstacles block vision of everything but kaiju

- ui
  - wasd + WASD movement
  - in motion, WASD gives slower adjustments
  - dedicated dismount button, always on the left
  - number key matches item index for weapon selection
  - indicate the mode: aiming weapon vs moving
    - while aiming: wasd to fire in that direction
  - inventory
    - there's a button to pick up an item
    - if your inventory is full, you pick an item to replace
    - the replaced item is gone
  - legend
  - log
  - mouseover or something for enemy hp/state?
    - display info about thing you last hit

- kaiju behaviors
  - sleep
  - chase the player
  - smack player around
  - break down obstacles that get in the way of chasing the player
    - fling the debris near the player
    - warning indicator: can dodge it
  - break down obstacles just because and fling debris at the player
  - beam attack?
    - telegraph charging
  - fire breath?
  - leap?
  - 

